docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON. A FEW weeks ago the chairmen of the two national political committees were brought together in Washington's Mayflower Hotel to conclude a solemn compact.

headline.main: Party Chairman: Study in Feuds and Funds; In one corner stands Mr. Butler, and in the other, Mr. Hall. The decision: Nov. 6. Party
